unately%20for%20the%20Fed%20chair%2C%20the%20second%20half%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20even%20tougher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20faces%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20circumstances.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariff-deadlines-august-rate-cuts-jerome-powell-inflation-economy-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Trump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20threaten%20to%20raise%20consumer%20prices%3B%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20showing%20some%20signs%20of%20cooling%20off.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dual%20threat%20sets%20up%20an%20epic%20and%20delicate%20conundrum%20for%20Powell%20and%20the%20central%20bank%20as%20they%20go%20about%20setting%20policy%2C%20according%20to%20Robert%20L.%20Hetzel%20and%20Joseph%20E.%20Gagnon%2C%20two%20former%20Fed%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20two%20mandates%20that%20can%20sometimes%20be%20at%20odds%3A%20keeping%20inflation%20in%20check%20and%20supporting%20the%20labor%20market.%20Its%20main%20tool%20to%20is%20its%20ability%20to%20set%20short-term%20interest%20rates.%20When%20inflation%20runs%20too%20hot%2C%20it%20cranks%20up%20rates%20to%20slow%20demand.%20When%20the%20labor%20market%20starts%20to%20unravel%2C%20it%20cuts%20rates%20to%20boost%20borrowing%20and%20spending%2C%20and%20in%20turn%2C%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fed%20funds%20rate%20has%20been%20above%204%25%20now%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20as%20the%20central%20bank%20sought%20to%20hamper%20rising%20prices.%20Against%20most%20forecasts%2C%20it%20had%20done%20so%20successfully%20without%20throwing%20the%20economy%20into%20recession.%20It%20had%20then%20begun%20to%20cut%20rates%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20stick%20the%20soft%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20Trump's%20tariffs%20came%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20Fed%20faces%20what%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20an%20unprecedented%20problem.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20some%20economists%20say%20the%20labor%20market%20looks%20set%20to%20soften%20further%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-cracking-job-market-layoffs-unemployment-recession-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20openings%20fall%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20as%20small%20businesses%20report%20slowing%20sales%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economic-outlook-job-market-hiring-data-revisions-tariffs-inflation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efalling%20hiring%20intentions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20here's%20a%20chart%20from%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research%20economist%20Neil%20Dutta%20showing%20the%20close%20relationship%20between%20weak%20small%20business%20sales%20and%20the%20unemployment%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22968%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22nfib%20poor%20sales%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6871284ff748d8c055f57387%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22726%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHaver%20Analytics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20slowing%20job%20market%20would%20usually%20not%20be%20accompanied%20by%20the%20threat%20of%20rising%20inflation%2C%20allowing%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates.%20But%20tariffs%20are%20complicating%20things.%20If%20the%20Fed%20jumps%20the%20gun%20with%20lowering%20rates%2C%20they%20could%20essentially%20be%20pouring%20gasoline%20on%20a%20fire%20that%20tariffs%20already%20threaten%20to%20stoke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Trump's%20import%20taxes%20haven't%20appeared%20to%20leak%20into%20consumer%20prices%20due%20to%20companies%20stockpiling%20inventory%20in%20late%202024%20and%20early%202025.%20But%20eventually%2C%20those%20firms%20will%20have%20to%20start%20passing%20on%20higher%20prices%20to%20customers%20as%20inventories%20run%20low%20and%20tariffs%20start%20to%20eat%20into%20profits%2C%20according%20to%20both%20Gagnon%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Peterson%20Institute%20for%20International%20Economics%20and%20a%20former%20associate%20director%20on%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Board%2C%20and%20Hetzel%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Richmond%20Fed%20from%201975-2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20raise%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Hetzel%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20always%20happens%20with%20a%20lag%20because%20nobody%20wants%20to%20be%20first%20and%20lose%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20the%20Fed%20faces%20in%20moving%20too%20early%20is%20potentially%20allowing%20consumer%20inflation%20expectations%20to%20become%20unanchored%2C%20Gagnon%20said.%20Higher%20prices%20then%20become%20a%20self-fulfilling%20prophecy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExpectations%20of%20inflation%20directly%20lead%20into%20inflation%20because%20then%20people%20are%20expecting%20other%20people%20to%20raise%20prices%2C%20they're%20quicker%20to%20raise%20their%20own%20prices%2C%20and%20the%20workers%20are%20quicker%20to%20ask%20for%20raises%20if%20they%20think%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20another%20burst%20of%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Gagnon%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you've%20got%20to%20keep%20that%20spiral%20from%20starting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20of%20moving%20the%20other%20way%20and%20raising%20rates%20to%20ensure%20inflation%20stays%20low%20could%20also%20have%20disastrous%20consequences%2C%20Hetzel%20said%2C%20and%20spark%20a%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20panic%26quot%3B%20as%20bond%20rates%20surge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Fed's%20in%20a%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20Hetzel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dilemma%20facing%20Powell%20is%20in%20some%20ways%20unprecedented%20because%20the%20last%20time%20the%20Fed%20had%20to%20face%20elevated%20tariffs%20was%20in%20the%201930s%20when%20the%20Smoot-Hawley%20Act%20was%20passed%2C%20Gagnon%20said.%20But%20a%20major%20difference%20was%20that%20back%20then%2C%20the%20economy%20was%20still%20recovering%20from%20the%20Great%20Depression%20and%20inflation%20pressures%20were%20not%20a%20concern%2C%20Gagnon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20aren't%20many%20direct%20parallels%20to%20the%20current%20environment%2C%20both%20Gagnon%20and%20Hetzel%20said%20tariff-driven%20inflation%20could%20behave%20like%20price%20gains%20in%20an%20oil%20shock.%20That%20is%2C%20prices%20will%20rise%20one%20time%20and%20then%20settle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20taking%20that%20approach%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20Fed%20runs%20the%20risk%20of%20letting%20consumer%20inflation%20expectations%20float%20away.%20This%20might%20be%20an%20especially%20high%20risk%20given%20that%20we're%20only%20a%20few%20years%20removed%20from%20the%20post-pandemic%20inflation%20surge%2C%20which%20is%20fresh%20in%20consumers'%20minds.%20It's%20still%20fresh%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20Fed%20leaders%20as%20well%2C%20as%20they%20had%20infamously%20insisted%20the%20episode%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Btransitory.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20we've%20just%20had%20a%20big%20burst%20of%20inflation%20that%20they%20thought%20was%20temporary%20and%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20more%20permanent%2C%26quot%3B%20Gagnon%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20people%20might%20be%20more%20primed%20to%20react%20to%20higher%20prices%2C%20and%20to%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20another%20bout%20of%20inflation%20for%20two%20or%20three%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cuts-inflation-jobs-jerome-powell-economy-recession-tariffs-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752399001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f7daa8594fce90018f7b90c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cuts-inflation-jobs-jerome-powell-economy-recession-tariffs-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20hasn't%20been%20an%20easy%20start%20to%202025%20for%20Jerome%20Powell.%20Unfortunately%20for%20the%20Fed%20chair%2C%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20even%20tougher.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cuts-inflation-jobs-jerome-powell-economy-recession-tariffs-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israeli%20F-15%20suffered%20fuel%20tank%20issue%20in%20Iran%2C%20nearly%20aborted%20mission%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752398804000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-122417505%2Cimgsize-21228.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F12-day-war-israeli-f-15-suffered-fuel-tank-issue-while-approaching-tehran-nearly-aborted-mission-report-says%2Farticleshow%2F122417175.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F122417175.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDuring%20the%2012-day%20war%20with%20Iran%2C%20an%20Israeli%20F-15%20faced%20a%20fuel%20issue%20near%20Tehran.%20The%20pilot%20detected%20the%20problem%20inside%20Iranian%20territory.%20A%20refueling%20aircraft%20was%20dispatched%20to%20assist.%20An%20emergency%20landing%20in%20a%20neighboring%20country%20was%20planned%20as%20an%20alternative.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20refueling%20was%20successful.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F12-day-war-israeli-f-15-suffered-fuel-tank-issue-while-approaching-tehran-nearly-aborted-mission-report-says%2Farticleshow%2F122417175.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F12-day-war-israeli-f-15-suffered-fuel-tank-issue-while-approaching-tehran-nearly-aborted-mission-report-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F122417175.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F12-day-war-israeli-f-15-suffered-fuel-tank-issue-while-approaching-tehran-nearly-aborted-mission-report-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F122417175.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk's%20xAI%20pressed%20employees%20to%20install%20surveillance%20software%20on%20personal%20laptops%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk's%20xAI%20is%20building%20a%20massive%20data%20center%20in%20Memphis.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eb173669253ccddf9ad3c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223150%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk's%20xAI%20is%20building%20a%20massive%20data%20center%20in%20Memphis.%3Cp%3EVincent%20Feuray%20%2F%20Hans%20Lucas%20%2F%20Hans%20Lucas%20via%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EXAI%20is%20rolling%20out%20employee%20surveillance%20software%20for%20the%20workers%20that%20train%20Grok.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20workers%20expressed%20concern%20after%20they%20were%20told%20to%20download%20it%20on%20their%20personal%20laptop.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EXAI%20adjusted%20its%20policy%20after%20an%20inquiry%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20allowing%20delays%20for%20those%20awaiting%20company%20devices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk's%20xAI%20told%20workers%20to%20download%20employee%20tracking%20software%20on%20their%20personal%20computers%2C%20prompting%20privacy%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20worker's%20apparent%20resignation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20startup%20told%20the%20tutors%20who%20train%20its%20Grok%20chatbot%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20they%20would%20be%20expected%20to%20download%20a%20workforce%20management%20system%20called%20Hubstaff%2C%20according%20to%20a%20document%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tutors%20were%20initially%20asked%20to%20download%20the%20software%20onto%20their%20personal%20computers%20by%20July%2011%20if%20they%20did%20not%20have%20a%20company-issued%20device%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document%20and%20sources%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20issue%20that%20asked%20to%20speak%20anonymously%20as%20they%20were%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20company's%20behalf.%20They%20were%20told%20to%20enable%20access%20to%20screen%20captures%2C%20and%20were%20also%20told%20that%20using%20the%20software%20was%20mandatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Business%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20xAI%20with%20questions%20about%20Hubstaff%2C%20xAI%20announced%20tweaks%20to%20the%20policy%20on%20Slack%3A%20Now%2C%20workers%20who%20requested%20company%20computers%20could%20wait%20to%20download%20the%20software%20until%20they%20receive%20a%20company-issued%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20employees%20who%20downloaded%20the%20software%20ahead%20of%20the%20July%2011%20deadline%20or%20purchased%20a%20new%20device%20would%20also%20be%20allowed%20to%20wait%20for%20an%20xAI%20computer%20to%20be%20shipped%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20said%20it%20will%20only%20use%20the%20system%20to%20monitor%20URL%20and%20application%20visits%20during%20designated%20work%20hours%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document.%20According%20to%20its%20website%2C%20Hubstaff%20can%20also%20track%20mouse%20movement%20and%20keystrokes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20new%20tool%20serves%20to%20streamline%20work%20processes%2C%20provide%20clearer%20insights%20into%20daily%20tutoring%20activities%2C%20and%20ensure%20resources%20align%20with%20Human%20Data%20priorities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20human%20resources%20team%20said%20in%20a%20mass%20email%20to%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHubstaff%20would%20be%20used%20to%20gauge%20employee%20performance%20and%20gather%20data%20on%20how%20tutors%20perform%20research%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20xAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20spoke%20up%20with%20privacy%20concerns%20about%20the%20software%2C%20according%20to%20Slack%20messages%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20One%20worker%20said%20they%20would%20resign%20due%20to%20the%20Hubstaff%20roll-out%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Slack%20message%20that%20received%20dozens%20of%20reactions%20appearing%20to%20support%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20message%2C%20the%20worker%20wrote%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bsurveillance%20disguised%20as%20productivity%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmanipulation%20masked%20as%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaff%20with%20concerns%20about%20data%20privacy%20on%20their%20personal%20computers%20had%20been%20told%20to%20either%20purchase%20a%20new%20computer%20using%20xAI's%20%2450%20per%20month%20tech%20stipend%20or%20create%20a%20separate%20log-in%20and%20profile%20on%20their%20device%20that%20would%20keep%20their%20work%20separate%20from%20any%20browsing%20in%20their%20personal%20time%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%2C%20which%20requires%20workers%20to%20clock%20in%20and%20out%2C%20would%20not%20track%20activity%20on%20the%20laptop%20outside%20of%20work%20hours%2C%20the%20document%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20supplies%20some%20workers%20with%20company-issued%20Chromebooks%2C%20but%20many%20workers%20use%20their%20personal%20devices%20for%20the%20role%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-hiring-ramp-up-data-annotators-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%20roll-out%2C%20tutors%20were%20initially%20told%20that%20the%20company%20had%20run%20out%20of%20Chromebooks%2C%20and%20it%20was%20unclear%20when%20they%20would%20be%20restocked%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20guidance%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20AI%20companies%20have%20used%20Hubstaff.%20In%20an%20ongoing%20worker%20lawsuit%20filed%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-ai-public-google-docs-security-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScale%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20alleged%20the%20company%20misclassified%20workers%2C%20a%20former%20employee%20said%20the%20company%20used%20Hubstaff%20to%20monitor%20data%20annotators%20and%20that%20they%20were%20required%20to%20download%20it%20onto%20their%20personal%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Scale%20AI%20said%20that%20the%20company%20uses%20Hubstaff%20%26quot%3Bto%20help%20contributors%20track%20the%20time%20they%20choose%20to%20spend%20on%20tasks%2C%20supporting%20accurate%20payment%20submissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Lowe%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20has%20brought%20cases%20against%20Musk-owned%20companies%20Tesla%20and%20X%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20while%20worker%20surveillance%20tactics%20can%20pose%20some%20legal%20risks%20for%20the%20company%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20risk%20often%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20company's%20reasoning%20for%20additional%20security%20practices%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20notice%2C%20and%20opportunities%20for%20reimbursement%20toward%20a%20separate%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20balancing%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXAI%20could%20make%20a%20case%20that%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Ban%20interest%20in%20trade%20secrets%20and%20ensuring%20employees%20are%20not%20violating%20privacy%20obligations%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowe%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20next%20step%20is%20to%20determine%20if%20there%20is%20a%20less%20intrusive%20way%20to%20accomplish%20that%20objective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%2C%20where%20xAI%20is%20headquartered%2C%20has%20some%20of%20the%20most%20stringent%20worker-protection%20laws%2C%20but%20many%20of%20the%20company's%20tutors%20are