C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20another%20company.%20Joining%20Microsoft%20was%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20so%20much%20effort%20into%20preparing%20for%20the%20interview%20process.%20If%20you%20told%20me%20as%20a%20little%20girl%20she'd%20be%20working%20for%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20in%20the%20world%2C%20she%20wouldn't%20have%20believed%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20year%20into%20working%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20I%20started%20considering%20getting%20a%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20my%20late%2020s%20that%20I%20realised%20what%20I%20was%20experiencing%20could%20be%20autism%20and%20ADHD.%20When%20I%20described%20my%20struggles%20to%20people%2C%20a%20few%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20had%20considered%20that%20I%20might%20be%20autistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnosed-with-autism-twenties-it-didnt-stop-me-from-success-2025-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DI%2527ve%2520always%2520sensed%2520there%2Cthat%2520felt%2520impossible%2520for%2520me.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediagnosed%20with%20autism%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2030.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20I%20also%20received%20an%20ADHD%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20helped%20me%20understand%20myself%20better.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jade%20Wilson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fa21185e81483682dbb55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJade%20Wilson%20typically%20wears%20headphones%20in%20the%20office%20to%20keep%20background%20noise%20from%20distracting%20her.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jade%20Wilson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20previous%20jobs%20where%20I%20had%20to%20go%20into%20the%20office%20regularly%2C%20I%20would%20get%20overstimulated%20without%20even%20realizing%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20get%20headaches%20from%20fluorescent%20office%20lighting.%20Background%20noise%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20focus%20during%20meetings.%20At%20my%20desk%2C%20I%20typically%20wore%20headphones%2C%20which%20meant%20I%20wasn't%20talking%20to%20my%20colleagues%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20found%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20move%20around.%20When%20I%20had%20to%20sit%20down%20in%20meetings%2C%20I'd%20get%20restless%20and%20need%20to%20doodle%20to%20keep%20myself%20engaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20working%20remotely%20for%20Microsoft%20has%20made%20a%20big%20difference.%20I%20still%20go%20into%20the%20office%20occasionally%2C%20but%20mostly%20work%20from%20home%20where%20I%20have%20a%20setup%20that%20works%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20avoid%20harsh%2C%20overhead%20lighting%20and%20rely%20on%20natural%20light%20instead.%20There's%20a%20walking%20pad%20under%20my%20desk%20for%20when%20I'm%20feeling%20restless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20in%20this%20industry%20still%20throws%20up%20challenges%2C%20but%20my%20diagnoses%20have%20helped%20me%20better%20understand%20my%20reactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22679b2bcc-7386-4afe-bcac-d6568b9169eb%5C%22%3EI've%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20life%20being%20told%20I'm%20rude%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-career-advice-luck-ex-meta-engineer-rahul-pandey-startup-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENetworking%20events%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20%E2%80%94%20and%20still%20are%20%E2%80%94%20difficult%20for%20me.%20I%20sometimes%20struggle%20to%20initiate%20conversations%20with%20strangers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20my%20diagnoses%2C%20I%20used%20to%20drink%20at%20these%20events%20as%20a%20coping%20mechanism.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20more%20accepting%20of%20myself.%20I%20don't%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20drink%2C%20and%20I%20give%20myself%20permission%20to%20leave%20a%20networking%20event%20early%20if%20I%20want%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20I%20communicate%20with%20colleagues%20is%20also%20challenging.%20People%20often%20tell%20me%20I'm%20rude%20when%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20I'm%20being%20direct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jade%20Wilson%20by%20Microsoft%20sign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686f9fdc3d5881a51c1d0c2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJade%20Wilson%20is%20a%20senior%20software%20engineer%20at%20Microsoft.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jade%20Wilson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20good%20at%20gap%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20spotting%20what's%20missing%2C%20identifying%20requirements%2C%20and%20building%20robust%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20autism%20shaped%20my%20interests%20and%20made%20me%20better%20at%20mathematics%2C%20which%20gave%20me%20the%20ability%20to%20identify%20gaps%20and%20gather%20requirements%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20a%20strength%20that%20can%20sometimes%20be%20misread.%20To%20others%2C%20it%20can%20look%20like%20I'm%20constantly%20finding%20flaws%20in%20everything%20when%20I'm%20trying%20to%20problem-solve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20mostly%20about%20how%20I%20ask%20questions%20at%20work.%20From%20my%20perspective%2C%20I'm%20just%20being%20thorough.%20Colleagues%20can%20take%20it%20as%20criticism%2C%20even%20though%20that's%20not%20my%20intention.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20being%20diagnosed%2C%20I've%20made%20more%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20consider%20how%20my%20words%20might%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20make%20sure%20when%20I'm%20writing%20things%20like%20emails%2C%20I%20remain%20factual%2C%20but%20consider%20the%20emotions%20that%20people%20might%20associate%20with%20certain%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sometimes%20struggle%20with%20cognitive%20empathy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ability%20to%20understand%20someone's%20emotions%20without%20having%20experienced%20them%20myself.%20I%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20engage%20with%20rational%20empathy%2C%20so%20I've%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20trying%20to%20rationalize%20how%20my%20wording%20could%20make%20someone%20else%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221107%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jade%20Wilson%20with%20Microsoft%20lanyard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686fa0143d5881a51c1d0c32%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221476%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJade%20Wilson%20said%20her%20work-from-home%20setup%20helps%2C%20but%20networking%20events%20are%20still%20a%20challenge.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jade%20Wilson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20colleague%20takes%20something%20the%20wrong%20way%2C%20I'll%20now%20explain%20that%20I'm%20autistic%20and%20have%20ADHD.%20I'll%20say%20something%20along%20the%20lines%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20mean%20it%20as%20criticism%2C%20and%20my%20preferred%20communication%20method%20is%20direct%20language.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20helps%20others%20understand%20that%20my%20communication%20might%20be%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20I%20think%20it%20has%20been%20taken%20well%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20has%20raised%20awareness%20of%20the%20struggles%20and%20strengths%20that%20people%20with%20autism%20and%20ADHD%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20constant%20communication%20with%20my%20manager%2C%20who%20is%20very%20supportive%2C%20and%20my%20team%2C%20too%2C%20and%20they've%20all%20been%20very%20open-minded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f61c3aa-2f5b-4fdd-a8f2-d45facae7733%5C%22%3EThe%20growth%20mindset%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20thing%20at%20Microsoft%20is%20the%20growth%20mindset%20%E2%80%94%20always%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20improve%20yourself%20regardless%20of%20your%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20on%20my%20communication%20is%20something%20I've%20been%20doing%20since%20finding%20out%20I'm%20autistic%20and%20have%20ADHD.%20For%20me%2C%20this%20is%20constant%20self-growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20people%20to%20understand%20that%20I'm%20not%20intentionally%20difficult%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20do%20a%20good%20job%20like%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20how%20people%20work%20and%20communicate%20differently.%20I%20don't%20call%20out%20neurotypical%20colleagues%20for%20being%20fluffy%20or%20abstract%20in%20their%20communication.%20I%20try%20to%20understand%20their%20point%20of%20view%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20they%20understand%20mine%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20awareness%20shouldn't%20stop%20with%20autism%2C%20ADHD%2C%20or%20other%20labels.%20It's%20about%20respecting%20everyone's%20differences%20and%20making%20the%20effort%20to%20understand%20perspectives%20that%20aren't%20our%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20being%20neurodiverse%20at%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzitser%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejzitser%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-navigate-work-microsoft-autism-adhd-diagnoses-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752398461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686f9dedf748d8c055f55467%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-navigate-work-microsoft-autism-adhd-diagnoses-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jade%20Wilson%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20received%20later-in-life%20autism%20and%20ADHD%20diagnoses.%20Big%20Tech%20networking%20events%20can%20pose%20a%20challenge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Nelken-Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A70%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-navigate-work-microsoft-autism-adhd-diagnoses-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%